## Harness map

This project follows the **three-beat lifecycle** — **Spec → Ship → Signal**. The Claude Code harness is in `.claude/` — copied from the blueprint's `claude-config/.claude/` bundle.

| Primitive | Location | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Slash commands | `.claude/commands/` | `/spec <idea\|epic\|feature\|fix\|chore>`, `/ship`, `/signal <init\|sync\|audit\|status>`, `/beat <status\|install\|update>` |
| Subagents | `.claude/agents/` | `spec-researcher`, `spec-author` |
| Skills | `.claude/skills/` | `australian-spelling`, `hard-rules-check`, `signal-sync` |
| Hooks | `.claude/hooks/` | `session-start`, `beat-aware-prompt`, `template-guard`, `pre-write-spelling`, `pre-commit-secret-scan`, `pre-commit-gate`, `prune-merged-branches` |
| Settings | `.claude/settings.json` | Permissions + hook wiring |
| Sacred templates | `docs/templates/` | Spec-driven document templates (Rule 4) |
| Reference contracts | `docs/contracts/` | Stack-agnostic interfaces: API envelope, error taxonomy, auth-token shape, telemetry schema (Rule 4) |

When in doubt, run `/beat` for a read-only status snapshot + the next-best command.

